 updated it, the one who forgot to tell the new analyst where to find the s=
preadsheet. In a fair world, that person would be as legendary as a trader =
who lost $600 million, and would have no trouble finding a new job. Someone=
 should hire this lawyer! Not great with details, but, for a lawyer, an abs=
olutely incredible familiarity with risk.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">T=
wo other things. First: This will cost Barclays 450 million pounds, but=C2=
=A0who will get the money?[3] Clearly part of the answer is: Barclays=E2=80=
