x 0;">VXX was trading at $48.04 a year ago; it was down to $28.81 on March =
14, when Barclays stopped selling more of it. If you bought VXX to bet that=
 volatility was going up, you lost =E2=80=94=C2=A0but if you bought at the =
right time and in the right way, you get to tear up your bet.=C2=A0Presumab=
ly the people who bought VXX directly from Barclays are mostly market maker=
s, and the biggest holders of VXX today are=C2=A0market makers.[4] I am not=
 sure exactly who will get to demand rescission on these trades, and I susp=
ect that people who bought from the market maker might also have a case. Bu=
t it would be funny if Barclays=E2=80=99s 450 million-pound loss was mostly=
 a random windfall for high-frequency traders who make markets in exchange-=
traded funds.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Second: Barclays did not noti=
